The paper discusses fault-tolerant real-time streaming, which involves network protocols and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses routing algorithms, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of FEC codes, which is related to information theory and coding, and falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions multi-path routing, which is related to multimedia systems and falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the overall link failure rate, which is related to system dynamics and control, and falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
